            "en": "<p>The training pathway to qualify as a type C energy expert, which is the subject of the application for accreditation, must meet the following conditions:</p><ol><li>Include substantive training, covering at least the legislative framework, the determination of the building’s energy performance index, the possible recommendations for cost-effective improvement of the building’s energy performance and the operation of the web application of the energy performance database.</li><li>Give at least one demo, using the web application to explain the procedure for accreditation as a type C energy expert and for drawing up an energy performance certificate for public buildings.</li></ol><p>In order to be accredited as an examination body by VEKA, the training institution is also required to submit an application for accreditation as an examination body to VEKA. The examination addresses at least the topics that are covered in the basic training.</p><p>Because the training institution exchanges <strong>personal data</strong> of the energy experts, the provisions of the Act of 30 July 2018 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data must be observed.</p>",
